[[Infrared]] radiation can be used to measure both the temperature of the surface (using &quot;window&quot; wavelengths to which the atmosphere is transparent), and the temperature of the atmosphere (using wavelengths for which the atmosphere is not transparent, or measuring cloud top temperatures in infrared windows).  
